msgctxt "#Tips_001"
msgid ""
"Build floodplain farms as close to the water as you can. If the flood is "
"poor, the farms will still be at least partially covered, and that way "
"retain more fertility."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_002"
msgid ""
"Try to sell goods like Papyrus and Linen as they have a low need in the city"
" and sell at relatively high prices."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_003"
msgid ""
"Land trade routes are much better than water trade routes, as they are not "
"dependent on having an open dock to trade at."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_004"
msgid ""
"If you are building directly on the Kingdom Road you will want to use "
"roadblocks to prevent your walkers from wandering away from where they are "
"needed."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_005"
msgid ""
"Because each city is limited to how much they can buy in a year, and because"
" you may produce a lot more finished products than they can buy, you may "
"want to sell off both finished products and raw materials."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_006"
msgid ""
"If you want to avoid creating Scribes in your city, just avoid distributing "
"luxury goods to prevent your houses from evolving into manors. This way, you"
" can provide all the other services like libraries and scribal schools for "
"high society, but keep a strong workforce."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_007"
msgid ""
"Be sure to always have extra temples and shrines built for your Patron God, "
"as they need the extra attention."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_008"
msgid ""
"Walkers have a 2-tile effect around them, meaning that a recruiter can find "
"occupied houses one tile away from the road he’s on."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_009"
msgid ""
"It’s better to respond late to a request than to ignore it completely - the "
"penalty will be less severe and sometimes, if the gods are willing, you "
"might even get away with it."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_010"
msgid ""
"Use the gameplay options to set up the game the way you enjoy it the most. "
"We’re just here to have fun and build pyramids."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_011"
msgid ""
"Until you’ve reached the last levels of housing, trade will bring way more "
"debens in than taxes."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_012"
msgid ""
"While food is consumed by inhabitants, goods are consumed by houses. As long"
" as you don't build new housing, there is no reason to produce more goods."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_013"
msgid ""
"While physicians are not required to evolve houses right away, they will "
"still protect your citizens from diseases."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_014"
msgid ""
"It takes 4 months for a fully staffed military recruiter to train 7 "
"soldiers. Build your forts early to avoid getting caught by unexpected "
"invasions."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_015"
msgid ""
"The Palace, your Mansion and the Festival Square are all unique and somewhat"
" expensive buildings. Plan your city accordingly."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_016"
msgid ""
"Distribution walkers seem to roam aimlessly along your road network, but "
"some roadblocks will allow you to control their path. A powerful tool, but "
"hard to set up."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_017"
msgid ""
"Building a city without roadblocks is quite a challenge; they are your most "
"powerful crowd-control tool, so never hesitate to abuse them!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_018"
msgid ""
"Meadow farms have different harvest dates, and some can even be harvested "
"twice a year."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_019"
msgid ""
"Use ctrl + left-click (by default) to copy/paste a building that is already "
"on the map. No need to go through the construction menu."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_020"
msgid ""
"The best kept egyptian secret is that hippos can dance, but ostriches have "
"the most swag."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_021"
msgid ""
"At the start of a mission, look at the world map to see what others cities "
"are willing to buy. Setting up the proper industries right off the bat will "
"allow you to export quickly and avoid money problems."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_022"
msgid ""
"New trade routes can open over time and can unlock access to previously "
"unavailable resources. On the other hand, some may close and deprive you of "
"important resources."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_023"
msgid ""
"Check your overseers of diversions, health, learning and temples for "
"information on coverage. Your Culture Rating is an aggregate of all of them."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_024"
msgid ""
"If there is only one way to go from the exit to the entry point of a "
"building, the walker will be forced to walk that path. Mastering this "
"technique can unlock new ways to organize your cities"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_025"
msgid ""
"Some tombs require the delivery of burial provisions. Check your overseer of"
" Monuments to see which resources are needed."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_026"
msgid ""
"Immigrants stop coming to your city when the City Sentiment is too low. Low "
"wages, high taxes, high unemployement or too many slums can be the main "
"reason for your people's discontent."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_027"
msgid ""
"You can put firehouses and architect posts everywhere just to be sure, but "
"clicking on a structure will tell you if it can actually catch fire or "
"collapse so you can spare some services buildings."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_028"
msgid ""
"The food output of fishing wharves depends on two parameters: the distance "
"between the wharf to the fish and the distance between the wharf and the "
"closest granary. Make sure one of them isn't slowing production down."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_029"
msgid ""
"Often, raw resources like clay or reeds can clutter your storage yards. Make"
" sure you have enough potters and papyrus maker to transform them all into "
"manufactured goods."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_030"
msgid ""
"If you cannot see behind a tall building, just activate flat mode using your"
" 'F' key (by default), the missing piece of road ruining your setup is "
"probably there."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_031"
msgid ""
"Too many events and notifications? These got their own tab in the options, "
"where you can choose what to display or hide and how."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_032"
msgid ""
"Instead of activating flatmode to see behind a building, you can also right "
"click on it to flatten it. Pressing the button (or the binded key) will "
"revert everything back to normal."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_033"
msgid ""
"If you’re colorblind or if the information is not clear enough in Overlays, "
"you can toggle an option to have building show columns that represent their "
"risks/access level."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#Tips_034"
msgid ""
"Events that will always be displayed no matter what are requests, invasions "
"and gifts. Everything else can be hidden, if you’re willing to take the risk"
" of missing something!"
msgstr ""
